RIYADH: Saudi Deputy Minister for Public Diplomacy Fahad Abualnasr met with Bahrain’s Ambassador to the Kingdom Shaikh Ali Abdulrahman bin Ali Al-Khalifa in Riyadh on Tuesday.
They reviewed diplomatic relations between the two brotherly countries and discussed topics of common interest.
The minister also attended another meeting presided by Saudi Arabia’s Deputy Foreign Minister Waleed Al-Khuraiji, President of the Inter-Parliamentary Union Duarte Pacheco, and the Portuguese Ambassador to the Kingdom Nuno Mathias in Riyadh.
During the meeting, they reviewed the strengthening of communication, cooperation and coordination on many issues of common concern, and the unification of parliamentary efforts in promoting international peace and security.